    <div class="content"><p>If you watched Life After People, you know much of the loss of human creations is due to the activity of living beings, most notably plants and bacteria. I think, based on the small corner of the planet we saw, the world was nuked so badly that hardly anything managed to survive. That could allow any number of things to survive the ravages of 2000 years, at least in the shape we saw.</p>
