    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/must-read-disappointing-interview-moore-and-others#comment-6616" class="active">Tomfoolery</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="http://www.lisapaitzspindler.com/blog" rel="nofollow">Lisa</a> (not verified) on Sat, 2009-01-17 19:45.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I don't think we can believe a single thing RDM says at this point and that's fine. I'm just going to sit back and be entertained. BSG got some real hardcore Science Fiction fans interested and those fans expected it to make sense on several levels. These are the people who are going to pull out the star-maps etc. and look for real scientific explanations for story elements. That's part of the fun for Science Fiction fans, but BSG isn't holding itself up to those standards and the backlash is due to this gap in expectations.  Wasn't it Sackoff who early on said something like the show was not really Science Fiction, but a drama in space (like Dallas?).</p>
<p>So who else thinks Ellen is going to mysteriously show up in Tigh's shower?</p>
