    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/must-read-disappointing-interview-moore-and-others#comment-6652" class="active">Alternate-Alternate Universe</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Anonymous (not verified) on Sun, 2009-01-18 16:23.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>The impression I got is it's Earth in the sense it's "Earth" but not "Earth, Earth". This is confusing and contradictory. It looks like the show painted its way into a corner and is trying to handwave itself out but it doesn't work. That's not some deep mystery, just bad writing. It's a show. It happens but I don't have to like it.</p>
<p>After my earlier bitching I'll add that the immersion bubble has popped for me. I'm less absorbed by the show, and discussing the technicalities and mythologies looks pointless if they pull stunts like that. It shouldn't be the job of the audience to figure that or deal with Deus Ex Machina shifting sands.</p>
<p>Now, rather than pull a big downer on your sub-blog, the angle I'm taking is to maintain my own integrity and ride this one out. Specifically, what's the best credible perspective and creative direction for me, and just enjoy the bubblegum train ride for what it is. It squares the circle so doesn't leave me bitching or feeling like my time is wasted.</p>
